President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Texas and ordered Federal assistance to help with the recovery efforts from the COVID-19 pandemic. This includes funding for Crisis Counseling for affected individuals, as well as emergency protective measures for the state and eligible local governments. George A. Robinson has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the State. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.